I've seen the schedule
for college coaches.

232
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:59,970
You think it'd be easier,
less grueling? It would not.

233
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,322
You don't know.
How do you know?

234
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:07,206
I just want you happy
and healthy,

235
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:12,689
and, yeah, home every once in a while,
just playing football with your own kids.

236
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:15,281
Going for a stupid walk
for hot chocolate,

237
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:18,484
maybe more than, you know,
twice a decade.

238
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,481
You... You're gonna get your record,
bro.

239
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:25,682
Even if Mickey has to steal it.

240
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:27,285
Forget about your dad.

241
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:30,529
You're 37 touchdowns away
from breaking a state record.

242
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,842
All right, it's about you.

243
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,890
Us.

244
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:39,088
Our year.
Our year.

245
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,520
Hold them high, boys. Hold them high.
DANNY: T.K.

246
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,845
What's up, big guy?
To your year. Chris, you, uh...

247
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:52,404
You're captain now. My man Danny
over here, he grew up on the team.

248
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,967
Has all the credit,
he doesn't need a title.

249
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,440
Kind of makes me wonder.

250
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:58,766
About what?

251
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,083
If it's gonna be your year,
or some other team's year.

252
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:05,011
K, we haven't lost a game...
I know, believe me.

253
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:09,603
I'm just saying, you guys gotta
open your eyes. You ain't ready.

254
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:12,410
On skills,
you have half the team we did.

255
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:16,326
On attitude, most of y'all got big heads
or just wanna wear the jersey.

256
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:19,689
So you gotta step up.
You gotta become real leaders.

257
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:24,044
You have to motivate your players
to get their game even tighter than ours.

258
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,604
Next year is on you.

259
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,210
Take care, boys.

260
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,447
Peace, man.
Yeah.

261
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,166
It's time to deal
with the De La Salle problem.

262
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,765
Last year,

263
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:49,410
De La Salle out-scored
league opponents 326 to 27.

264
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:54,003
Their average score
against league teams was 47 to 4.

265
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:58,166
How, Bob? How are we supposed
to compete against a program

266
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:01,762
that pulls in the best players
with the wave of a scholarship?

267
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,291
For the hundredth time,

268
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:07,605
De La Salle High's code of conduct
forbids scholarshipping athletes.

269
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:11,282
Explain to me why
the best wide receiver in my district

270
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:14,051
rides a bus for a solid hour
up to De La Salle.

271
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:17,204
Our program attracts great athletes,
plain and simple.

272
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:21,849
No matter how you get your players,
you're stacking your team with talent.

273
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,560
That's not cheating?
Let me get this straight.

274
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:27,286
You wanna penalize
us for building a winning program?

275
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:32,726
I'm done with this! Nobody wins 151
football games straight without cheating!

276
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:36,686
We will not play De La Salle
next season.

277
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:41,289
[MEN MURMURING]

278
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:45,490
Great. Done.
We don't wanna play you either.

279
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,883
We'll play
our five league games,

280
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:52,483
then we'll fill our open slots with
tougher teams from bigger conferences.

281
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:56,207
Gee, seems like I heard the 49ers
already have a full schedule.

282
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:57,845
MEN: Ha, ha, ha.
Who's left?

283
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,131
Long Beach Poly.

284
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:03,210
[MEN MURMURING]

285
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:08,566
Heh. Eidson, Poly's the number-one
high-school team in Southern California.

286
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,364
Yeah. Isn't it great?

287
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,327
[WHISPERS]
Poly?

288
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:15,126
We talked about this.
Never said you set it up.

289
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:17,926
Nationally, we're number one.
They're number two.

290
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:20,646
They've been trying to get us
on their schedule.

291
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,171
They're not afraid of us.

292
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:26,251
Guys, can't wait to see you play Poly.

293
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,606
Good luck.

294
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,531
[MEN MURMURING]

295
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:33,882
You can thank me later.

296
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:37,491
