00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:59,288
and sometimes holler?
That's right.

346
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:02,165
And one time,
Cam said you said the S-word.

347
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:03,566
I remember that time.

348
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:07,566
JAMAL: Well, here, you gotta be real quiet.
My mom's resting.

349
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,848
BOB:
Shh. Not a peep.

350
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:23,490
Hey, coach.
Cam, look.

351
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,800
Oh, man, that is tight.

352
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,642
Watch Mama, all right?

353
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:32,728
See, Mama?

354
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,445
<i>BOB:
How is she?</i>

355
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:40,050
The nurse say, um,

356
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,042
it's just a matter of time.

357
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:47,921
And that's it.
That's the last of my Mohicans.

358
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:50,728
You have Jamal.

359
00:20:51,840 --> 00:20:54,207
The boy don't know it yet,

360
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:57,410
but he's going down to San Jose,
stay with my cousin.

361
00:20:57,600 --> 00:21:01,286
They should be good to him,
but ain't got no room for me.

362
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:04,801
