to come see me, all right?

411
00:24:58,520 --> 00:24:59,965
I want 100 from you.

412
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:01,771
I still can't believe it.

413
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,644
Coach Lad smoking.

414
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:09,251
Mrs. Lad. Good seeing you.
So great to see you.

415
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:13,644
Take care of the big guy for me.
Okay, I will. Thanks for coming, Maurice.

416
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:16,684
Hey, you.
Hey, Dad.

417
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:19,162
Don't look so tough now, huh?
Heh, heh, heh.

418
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:22,123
DOCTOR:
Mr. Ladouceur.

419
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:26,689
Eighty-three percent occlusion
in your PLA descending artery.

420
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:29,202
We call that the widow-maker.

421
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,971
You're a very lucky man.
Yeah.

422
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:35,642
So, what happens next?
Recuperation.

423
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:39,926
Near-term, I'll be happy
if you're in good condition by April.

424
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:41,360
That's spring practice.

425
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:43,727
Not for you.

426
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:46,685
You've got five stents
and one shot to heal.

427
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,928
Stepping onto a field before summer?

428
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:51,248
Don't even think about it.

429
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:55,650
Dad, you're gonna coach me
next season, right?

430
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:58,004
Danny.

431
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:01,569
Danny.

432
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,726
