what it's like to never lose.

705
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,849
Today, I am lost.

706
00:42:39,040 --> 00:42:41,168
WOMAN 1:
Lord, have mercy.

707
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:45,449
It's as if life has taken
more than it gives,

708
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:48,328
and I don't know if I can handle it.

709
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:51,122
Lord, I'm struggling.

710
00:42:53,040 --> 00:42:55,281
I wanna understand why.

711
00:42:55,560 --> 00:42:57,722
Why Terrance?
WOMAN 2: Yes, Lord.

712
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,604
BOB:
Why now?

713
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:04,806
If we are to call ourselves Christians,
we cannot ask these questions

714
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:08,766
because to do so is to question
your benevolence, your divine wisdom.

715
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:11,769
But today I am lost.

716
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:15,089
Mr. Kelly,

717
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:16,806
T-Gram,

718
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:20,289
I can't even imagine your pain
right now.

719
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:24,406
But you raised the kind of young man
we all strive for.

720
00:43:25,840 --> 00:43:27,604
We ask our players...

721
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:31,524
to learn and embrace ideals,

722
00:43:31,720 --> 00:43:33,848
perfection, commitment,

723
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:37,442
compassion, brotherhood, faith.

724
00:43:37,640 --> 00:43:41,361
From the first time T.K. came
across that field, I saw it.

725
00:43:41,560 --> 00:43:45,929
A kid whose grace
wasn't just athletic,

726
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:48,122
but genuine in so many ways.

727
00:43:50,080 --> 00:43:51,923
He embodied those ideals.

728
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:53,963
WOMAN 3:
Yes, Lord.

729
00:43:55,200 --> 00:43:57,851
You never gave up
on anything or anyone.

730
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:02,051
And I did not teach you.

731
00:44:04,040 --> 00:44:05,963
You taught me.

732
00:44:08,240 --> 00:44:09,526
Thank you,

733
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:12,965
because when on some other day
I am lost

734
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:17,210
and struggling to keep my faith,
I need only remember you.

735
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:22,121
And for reasons we are not privy to,
God wanted T.K. home.

736
00:44:22,320 --> 00:44:24,322
He is with him now.

737
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:26,928
May God bless you.

738
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:32,043
<i>♪♪♪</i>

739
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,725
Cam.

740
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:47,207
Doesn't make no sense, coach.

741
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:51,000
I don't know what I'm supposed to do
anymore.

742
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,524
You stick to the plan.

743
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,370
Go to Oregon.

744
00:44:57,280 --> 00:45:00,124
<i>♪♪♪</i>

745
00:45:10,960 --> 00:45:14,169
Mowing the lawn?
What are you doing out here?

746
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:15,965
Dancing at our wedding.

747
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:18,242
With your dad.

748
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:21,689
He grins, looks over.
You were talking with the priest.

749
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:25,441
I remember, he leans in and said:

750
00:45:25,640 --> 00:45:29,804
"if you didn't know better, which one
puts the collar on every morning?"

751
00:45:30,320 --> 00:45:31,446
[CHUCKLES]

752
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:36,325
The music stops.

753
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:40,327
The dance is over.

754
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:45,450
And I'm heading over to rescue you.

755
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:48,162
<i>♪♪♪</i>

756
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:51,924
And he said something
I still remember.

757
00:45:53,280 --> 00:45:54,884
What's that?

758
00:45:57,960 --> 00:46:00,566
"I hope you won't be too lonely."

759
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:03,610
Your dad raised you.

760
00:46:03,800 --> 00:46:05,723
He loved you,

761
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:08,765
but when he died,

762
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:13,250
I think he felt like
he didn't really know you.

763
00:46:14,520 --> 00:46:18,081
Till a minute ago,
I thought that might happen to me too.

764
00:46:20,320 --> 00:46:23,881
I was sitting up, watching you sleep,
and it hit me.

765
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:30,610
Some people don't know
who they are,

766
00:46:30,800 --> 00:46:32,723
all that they have.

767
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:35,851
They just know something's missing.

768
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:41,451
So I was just sitting out here...

769
00:46:45,680 --> 00:46:48,411
getting ready to let you go again.

770
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:56,408
[WHISTLE BLOWS
AND PLAYERS GRUNTING]

771
00:46:57,040 --> 00:46:58,804
No, still way too slow.

772
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:02,328
You need to blow off the ball.
Faster step. Strike with intent.

773
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:04,249
[WHISTLE BLOWS
AND PLAYERS GRUNTING]

774
00:47:04,400 --> 00:47:09,327
On Friday, we play a football team that's
been preparing for this game for a year.

775
00:47:09,520 --> 00:47:13,809
You're not hitting with intensity,
conditioning with discipline.

776
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,923
Salinas, pull your weight.
Come on.

777
00:47:16,120 --> 00:47:18,407
TERRY: Oh, you're dogging it.
You're dogging it.

778
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:21,564
Commitment.
TERRY: Bellevue is bigger and stronger.

779
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:24,969
Accountability. Perfect effort.
Finally, love.

780
00:47:26,120 --> 00:47:29,761
This bond is what has led Spartans
to achieve far more than anyone,

781
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:32,804
including themselves,
believed they were capable of.

782
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:35,082
Six, seven.

783
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:37,760
Without it,
you may continue to win games.

784
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:39,809
Rep it out, Tayshon.
Four more.

785
00:47:40,040 --> 00:47:43,010
But you will have lost the chance
to become Spartans.

786
00:47:44,320 --> 00:47:45,970
Eight's good.

787
00:47:48,440 --> 00:47:52,445
ANNOUNCER: <i>Welcome to Seattle,
where the 2004 season opens</i>

788
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:56,321
<i>with a matchup between two of
the best teams in the country.</i>

789
00:48:00,360 --> 00:48:01,441
Come on! Whoo!

790
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:03,404
[CROWD CHEERING]

791
00:48:03,560 --> 00:48:05,130
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

792
00:48:05,360 --> 00:48:07,124
[PLAYERS GRUNTING]

793
00:48:07,320 --> 00:48:10,847
The powerhouse De La Salle Spartans
and their national record,

794
00:48:11,040 --> 00:48:14,249
151-game winning streak,
Keep the streak alive!

795
00:48:14,440 --> 00:48:17,523
<i>Taking on defending
Washington State champs, Bellevue.</i>

796
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:18,721
[CHANTING INDISTINCTLY]

797
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:22,771
Down, set, hut!

798
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:28,366
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

799
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:32,206
Strong right, lead at two.
Veer, pass, drag. Let's go.

800
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:35,811
PLAYER:
Strong left! Strong left!

801
00:48:36,240 --> 00:48:40,040
Open back 11. Back 11.
SALINAS: Down, set, hut!

802
00:48:45,680 --> 00:48:47,603
<i>Rick Salinas
throws a perfect pass,</i>

803
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:50,963
connecting with Danny Ladouceur
for a 13-yard gain.

804
00:48:51,160 --> 00:48:52,924
SALINAS:
Sixteen mid-line on one. Ready?

805
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:56,446
Go get them, Beast.

806
00:48:56,640 --> 00:49:01,362
ANNOUNCER: <i>Chris Ryan. This man has the size
and speed to play anywhere in the country.</i>

807
00:49:01,560 --> 00:49:04,325
SALINAS:
Red dog! Red dog! Set, hut-hut!

808
00:49:04,520 --> 00:49:07,410
<i>♪♪♪</i>

809
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:13,525
Go, go, go! Come on, Chris!
Come on, Chris!

810
00:49:13,760 --> 00:49:16,923
Come on, Beast! Come on, Beast!
Come on, Beast!

811
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:19,009
That's it! Yeah!

812
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:22,488
ANNOUNCER: <i>Chris Ryan, showing off
his ability, breaks a 45-yard run</i>

813
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:26,162
<i>to give De La Salle a 7-to-0 lead.</i>

814
00:49:26,400 --> 00:49:30,530
That's a great run, but our left tackle
needs to seal that backer better.

815
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:34,088
ANNOUNCER: <i>Ryan has been a scoring
machine, amassing 52 touchdowns</i>

816
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:36,608
<i>in his sophomore and junior seasons.</i>

817
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:39,562
<i>He is now 36 touchdowns away</i>

818
00:49:39,760 --> 00:49:43,560
from breaking
the California career touchdown record.

819
00:49:43,760 --> 00:49:45,762
QUARTERBACK:
Twenty-two. Hut, set, hut!

820
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:49,724
Beaser!

821
00:49:51,160 --> 00:49:53,891
This is like the drill we run every day
at practice!

822
00:49:54,080 --> 00:49:56,811
Shed that block
and get to the ball carrier!

823
00:49:57,840 --> 00:49:59,251
Okay.

824
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:00,851
SALINAS:
They're changing it up.

825
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:03,646
They're in man to man,
then dropping to cover two.

826
00:50:03,840 --> 00:50:06,320
Why don't you simplify it?
Read the free safety.

827
00:50:06,560 --> 00:50:08,688
Free safety will tell you everything.
CROWD: Whoo!

828
00:50:08,840 --> 00:50:11,002
What? Someone break one?

829
00:50:11,200 --> 00:50:13,009
Stop him! Stop him!

830
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:15,481
Get after him!

831
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:18,930
Ah, jeez!

832
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:20,167
[CROWD CHEERING]

833
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:23,767
Bellevue's Taylor King
breaks a 76-yard touchdown.

834
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:26,645
<i>This Bellevue team
is not afraid of De La Salle.</i>

835
00:50:26,840 --> 00:50:29,366
<i>We may just have a game here.</i>

836
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:34,000
<i>♪♪♪</i>

837
00:50:38,320 --> 00:50:40,129
[CROWD CHEERING]

838
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:44,004
And yet another completion.
First down, Bellevue.

839
00:50:45,520 --> 00:50:47,249
They're playing exactly like us.

840
00:50:48,240 --> 00:50:51,289
This Wolverine passing attack
is shredding De La Salle.

841
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:54,042
It's a three-deep and you got beat?

842
00:50:54,280 --> 00:50:57,727
Your responsibility is the quarterback
when they run the option.

843
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:00,810
Right? We practiced all of this,
come on, now!

844
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:02,126
[ALL GRUNTING]

845
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:06,487
You have to break down
to make that stop.

846
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:08,967
Don't get caught flat-footed.

847
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:15,325
No, no, no!

848
00:51:15,760 --> 00:51:18,604
Stop him! Stop him!

849
00:51:18,840 --> 00:51:20,171
God!

850
00:51:20,360 --> 00:51:22,203
Here's something nobody expected.

851
00:51:22,400 --> 00:51:26,291
The Wolverines are controlling the line
of scrimmage against De La Salle.

852
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:29,921
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

853
00:51:30,080 --> 00:51:32,845
They're beating us off the ball
on every snap.

854
00:51:33,640 --> 00:51:36,723
PLAYER 1: Down.
QUARTERBACK: Blue 22! Blue 22!

855
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:38,001
Set.

856
00:51:38,240 --> 00:51:39,844
PLAYER 2:
Go left! Go left!

857
00:51:40,040 --> 00:51:41,280
Hut!

858
00:51:47,400 --> 00:51:50,768
ANNOUNCER: <i>Bellevue scores to give
the Washington State champions</i>

859
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:54,766
a <i>28-to-7 lead
over powerhouse De La Salle.</i>

860
00:51:55,000 --> 00:51:56,331
[CROWD CHEERING]

861
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:58,084
We're gonna lose.

862
00:52:00,280 --> 00:52:01,281
Argh!

863
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:07,882
Hit Danny on a 12-yard curl in the seam
between the linebacker and the safety.

864
00:52:11,440 --> 00:52:13,602
Down, set, hike!

865
00:52:18,840 --> 00:52:23,687
ANNOUNCER: <i>Oh! Danny Ladouceur drops</i> a <i>pass.
His dad will not be happy about that.</i>

866
00:52:23,880 --> 00:52:25,803
MICKEY:
Gotta get it to the players.

867
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:28,128
He's gotta catch it, Bev.

868
00:52:28,600 --> 00:52:31,251
SALINAS:
Ready. Set, hut!

869
00:52:35,240 --> 00:52:37,402
ANNOUNCER: <i>Ladouceur's hit
and coughs up the ball!</i>

870
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:39,409
Gotta hold on to that ball,
Danny!

871
00:52:39,960 --> 00:52:42,725
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Bellevue recovers. Bellevue recovers.</i>

872
00:52:42,920 --> 00:52:46,083
<i>♪♪♪</i>

873
00:52:57,280 --> 00:52:59,601
[CROWD CHEERING]

874
00:53:07,520 --> 00:53:12,128
I don't care how good you think you are!
I'm the best receiver on this team.

875
00:53:12,960 --> 00:53:16,806
I ran my route, they attacked, man.
Ran the ball right by you.

876
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:18,087
[CHEERING]

877
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:22,806
CHRIS: Come on! Let's go, let's go!
CROWD: Eight, seven,

878
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:25,401
six, five, four,

879
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:28,365
Down, hut!
CROWD: three, two, one.

880
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:29,647
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

881
00:53:29,800 --> 00:53:32,360
ANNOUNCER: <i>And that's it. The
streak is over! The streak is over!</i>

882
00:53:32,560 --> 00:53:36,565
<i>The longest winning streak
in sports history is now over</i>

883
00:53:36,760 --> 00:53:40,446
<i>As the Bellevue Wolverines
have shocked the De La Salle Spartans</i>

884
00:53:40,640 --> 00:53:45,646
<i>in perhaps the biggest upset
in high-school football history.</i>

885
00:53:46,680 --> 00:53:49,251
<i>♪♪♪</i>

886
00:53:56,600 --> 00:53:59,763
<i>♪♪♪</i>

887
00:54:16,120 --> 00:54:18,646
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

888
00:54:31,240 --> 00:54:33,607
Are you okay? It's okay.

889
00:54:34,480 --> 00:54:36,881
[ARTURO SOBBING]

890
00:54:48,840 --> 00:54:49,887
[BANGING]

891
00:54:50,040 --> 00:54:52,805
Hey, hey! We don't do that here.

892
00:54:53,480 --> 00:54:55,323
We don't do that.

893
00:54:59,200 --> 00:55:02,522
Reporters, friends, family, strangers.

894
00:55:02,720 --> 00:55:04,768
They're all gonna ask the same thing:

895
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:06,450
"What happened?"

896
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:09,007
This is a question
that's gonna follow you.

897
00:55:09,240 --> 00:55:11,322
"How did you lose the streak?"

898
00:55:11,520 --> 00:55:15,047
And every time,
you're gonna answer the truth:

899
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:19,131
"Bellevue played better than us
and we lost a high-school football game."

900
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:21,489
That's football.

901
00:55:22,080 --> 00:55:24,048
But it's not you.

902
00:55:25,520 --> 00:55:28,444
Don't let a game define who you are.

903
00:55:28,640 --> 00:55:31,689
Let the way you live your lives do that.

904
00:55:35,960 --> 00:55:37,371
Coach.

905
00:55:40,800 --> 00:55:44,566
I truly believe that life's most
impressionable lessons

906
00:55:44,760 --> 00:55:47,331
are ones where something bad
happens to you

907
00:55:47,520 --> 00:55:50,444
or something challenging
confronts you.

908
00:55:51,680 --> 00:55:55,969
No one can climb into your head and hear
what that little voice is saying to you.

909
00:55:56,680 --> 00:55:59,968
Is it saying,
"Oh, no, we lost the streak"?

910
00:56:00,640 --> 00:56:02,085
Well, what's it gonna say?

911
00:56:02,800 --> 00:56:06,646
After today, you're gonna find out
a lot about yourselves.

912
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:11,291
And you know something, we're all
gonna find out what this team is made of.

913
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:22,084
<i>BOB: The effort you put in during
the off-season was commendable.</i>

914
00:56:22,240 --> 00:56:23,844
[CROWD CHEERING]

915
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:29,206
But it has not translated onto the field.

916
00:56:32,880 --> 00:56:35,167
You've got to decide
what you wanna be.

917
00:56:35,360 --> 00:56:40,207
I get the feeling from you as a team
that you just wanna hop on that throne

918
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:43,051
<i>and place the championship ring
on your finger.</i>

919
00:56:43,240 --> 00:56:45,527
That you're at De La Salle
and deserve that.

920
00:56:46,040 --> 00:56:49,442
<i>For the most part, we're inconsistent,
mistake-prone, ragged,</i>

921
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:51,961
<i>and not very physical.</i>

922
00:56:52,960 --> 00:56:54,644
That's where we are.

923
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:57,844
As much as you don't wanna hear it,
that's my assessment.

924
00:56:58,040 --> 00:57:01,761
Do I feel like you can pull this off
and earn the right to that throne?

925
00:57:01,960 --> 00:57:03,962
Yeah, I do.
TERRY: Attaboy, attaboy!

926
00:57:04,160 --> 00:57:07,130
I'm not hoping you play well
against Clayton Valley.

927
00:57:07,360 --> 00:57:10,603
You have to.
You have to play well this week.

928
00:57:10,800 --> 00:57:14,885
Even if you step it up and play at your
ability level, it still won't be easy.

929
00:57:15,080 --> 00:57:18,163
<i>You're gonna have to fight
for victories in those games.</i>

930
00:57:18,360 --> 00:57:19,407
[PLAYERS GRUNTING]

931
00:57:19,560 --> 00:57:21,483
MICKEY:
All right, that's it, that's it!

932
00:57:23,280 --> 00:57:27,126
TERRY:
Oh, he's got a seam! Go, go, go!

933
00:57:27,320 --> 00:57:28,924
Nice work.
MICKEY: Oh, for...!

934
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:31,563
Argh!

935
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:35,043
ANNOUNCER: <i>Despite</i> a <i>well-played
game, De La Salle comes up short,</i>

936
00:57:35,240 --> 00:57:38,528
<i>and after two games,
is still winless in this young season.</i>

937
00:57:38,760 --> 00:57:43,049
<i>Bob Ladouceur's gonna have to figure
something out to get this team on track</i>

938
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:45,971
<i>if they plan on making it
to the playoffs this year.</i>

939
00:57:46,160 --> 00:57:47,491
[CHATTERING]

940
00:57:53,800 --> 00:57:55,290
BOB:
Pick up your heads.

941
00:57:55,480 --> 00:57:57,687
Meet me at the locker room tomorrow.

942
00:57:57,880 --> 00:57:59,405
Eight a.m.

943
00:58:12,200 --> 00:58:13,486
WOMAN:
What's up, Alex?

944
00:58:16,040 --> 00:58:19,123
CHRIS: Miss you. I'm all sweaty.
It's okay. It was a tough game.

945
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:22,488
Party is tomorrow, if you wanna go.

946
00:58:22,720 --> 00:58:24,802
CHRIS:
Maybe. I don't know. If you do.

947
00:58:25,000 --> 00:58:27,048
Are you kidding me?
Dad, please.

948
00:58:27,240 --> 00:58:30,005
You let some punk pull you
down at the two-yard line.

949
00:58:30,200 --> 00:58:33,044
I scored three touchdowns.
How many did you promise?

950
00:58:33,280 --> 00:58:35,328
Mr. Ryan, please.
Laurie, stop.

951
00:58:35,520 --> 00:58:38,000
Forty-one blast. Run it, now.

952
00:58:38,240 --> 00:58:41,005
Dad, it's midnight. I'm tired.
So am I.

953
00:58:41,240 --> 00:58:44,449
Forty-one blast. Run it, now.
You run it!

954
00:58:44,600 --> 00:58:45,647
Unh!

955
00:58:47,720 --> 00:58:49,529
MICKEY:
You listen close.

956
00:58:49,720 --> 00:58:51,961
I want that record.

957
00:58:52,160 --> 00:58:54,640
He's not gonna get it for you
with a busted rib.

958
00:58:54,880 --> 00:58:55,961
Now let him go.

959
00:58:57,160 --> 00:59:01,165
Hey, coach. Let's you and me
huddle up for a second, okay?

960
00:59:01,360 --> 00:59:04,489
I don't usually huddle up
with parents, Mick.

961
00:59:05,960 --> 00:59:08,691
<i>♪♪♪</i>

962
00:59:20,360 --> 00:59:21,566
[SIGHS]

963
00:59:29,440 --> 00:59:31,886
You think
this is gonna freak them out?

964
00:59:32,080 --> 00:59:34,321
I certainly hope so.

965
00:59:34,480 --> 00:59:37,609
<i>♪♪♪</i>

966
00:59:49,080 --> 00:59:50,809
<i>♪ When you're on top of the world ♪</i>

967
00:59:50,960 --> 00:59:54,726
<i>♪ Every man and every girl
No one ever come around your way ♪</i>

968
00:59:54,880 --> 00:59:59,681
<i>♪ When you're sitting on the corner
No one ever gonna pay you
Any mind that day ♪</i>

969
00:59:59,840 --> 01:00:05,483
<i>♪ Like a piece of your mind
That was stolen in time
Never listen what nobody say ♪</i>

970
01:00:07,480 --> 01:00:09,209
Good morning, Carol.
Hi, Bob.

971
01:00:10,720 --> 01:00:14,964
Nurse Ballard is a friend of mine. She's
in charge of the entire nursing staff.

972
01:00:15,360 --> 01:00:18,091
Today, we will be following her orders.

973
01:00:18,280 --> 01:00:21,841
Coach Lad and I worked at the Juvenile
Detention Center in Richmond.

974
01:00:22,040 --> 01:00:24,566
It was a little longer ago
than I'd rather admit.

975
01:00:24,800 --> 01:00:27,804
So you guys play a tough game.
Anybody ever been injured?

976
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:35,482
You've never been injured?

977
01:00:36,160 --> 01:00:39,721
It's part of the game. You don't think
about it, you bounce back.

978
01:00:40,360 --> 01:00:42,249
You're very brave.

979
01:00:42,440 --> 01:00:43,930
This is not that.

980
01:00:44,160 --> 01:00:49,200
Here, nobody bounces. Break into three
groups. When you hear your name,

981
01:00:49,400 --> 01:00:53,610
follow the nurse who called it
to the appropriate unit. Let's go.

982
01:00:54,680 --> 01:00:58,924
Nurse Adams is in charge of the Recovery
Ward, and she will take over from here.

983
01:00:59,560 --> 01:01:02,769
Good afternoon, gentlemen.
Welcome to the VA Recovery Ward.

984
01:01:02,960 --> 01:01:05,008
So here we specialize
in transplants,

985
01:01:05,400 --> 01:01:09,291
amputations and general rehabilitation
for limb recovery.

986
01:01:09,480 --> 01:01:14,441
Our focus here is on full recovery,
body and spirit.

987
01:01:14,800 --> 01:01:17,724
If this is too hard for anybody,
don't come in.

988
01:01:17,960 --> 01:01:19,689
Why would it be?

989
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:22,562
<i>♪♪♪</i>

990
01:01:22,880 --> 01:01:25,281
All our patients
are here for rehabilitation.

991
01:01:25,480 --> 01:01:30,168
Our job is to help them recover
from injuries received during combat.

992
01:01:30,360 --> 01:01:35,366
It's long and difficult, but we're dedicated
to getting them back to functioning lives.

993
01:01:35,560 --> 01:01:37,642
Hey, May.
MAY: Hey.

994
01:01:40,920 --> 01:01:42,524
[PHONE RINGING]

995
01:01:45,560 --> 01:01:46,800
Hello?

996
01:01:47,000 --> 01:01:48,331
I'll be right there.

997
01:01:48,520 --> 01:01:51,171
Hey, would you do me a favor?
Would you finish up?

998
01:01:53,200 --> 01:01:54,850
Thanks.

999
01:01:55,040 --> 01:01:57,407
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1000
01:02:14,520 --> 01:02:16,124
What are you looking at?

1001
01:02:16,560 --> 01:02:18,528
Oh, no, no, I just, um...

1002
01:02:18,720 --> 01:02:20,290
You just what?
Nothing.

1003
01:02:20,480 --> 01:02:22,005
What's the matter, boy?

1004
01:02:22,200 --> 01:02:24,248
Get on. Pace me.

1005
01:02:24,520 --> 01:02:26,727
What?
You do speak English, right?

1006
01:02:26,920 --> 01:02:28,160
Get on, pace me.

1007
01:02:43,880 --> 01:02:47,771
Ah!
Ah! What? What did I do? Did I hurt you?

1008
01:02:48,080 --> 01:02:51,323
Heh, heh. No, I'm just messing
with you, man.

1009
01:02:51,520 --> 01:02:53,602
I can't feel anything.

1010
01:02:54,040 --> 01:02:56,566
Heh. Wow.

1011
01:02:57,160 --> 01:02:58,730
Man, I...

1012
01:02:58,960 --> 01:03:02,248
Sometimes my legs hurt so bad,
I'd wish I didn't feel anything.

1013
01:03:02,440 --> 01:03:05,410
No, you don't.

1014
01:03:07,360 --> 01:03:10,887
No, I don't.

1015
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:14,762
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1016
01:03:16,720 --> 01:03:20,645
What's wrong with you, boy? You blind?
My bad, man. I didn't see you.

1017
01:03:20,840 --> 01:03:24,925
No, man. I swear I didn't even see you.
Hey, what the...? Hey! Hey, man!

1018
01:03:25,120 --> 01:03:27,646
Ha, ha, ha.
Is that...? Was that pee?

1019
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:29,683
Well, it sure ain't no Gatorade.
Ha, ha.

1020
01:03:29,880 --> 01:03:30,961
Oh, heck, no!

1021
01:03:31,200 --> 01:03:32,486
Hey, nurse!

1022
01:03:32,680 --> 01:03:33,966
Come on, man!

1023
01:03:38,840 --> 01:03:40,922
Come on, Danny.
You gotta speed this up.

1024
01:03:41,080 --> 01:03:42,320
[BEEPING]

1025
01:03:42,480 --> 01:03:44,448
All right.
Let him catch up, though.

1026
01:03:44,640 --> 01:03:47,166
Oh, great. You're a real gentleman.

1027
01:03:47,320 --> 01:03:48,560
[BEEPING]

1028
01:03:49,160 --> 01:03:50,161
On, baby.

1029
01:03:50,320 --> 01:03:51,367
[BEEPING]

1030
01:03:51,520 --> 01:03:53,363
Stop. Salinas. Quit it.

1031
01:03:54,440 --> 01:03:57,250
Salinas, enough.
I don't know if it is fast enough.

1032
01:03:57,800 --> 01:03:59,325
Show me what you got.

1033
01:04:00,200 --> 01:04:02,931
Let's go, Danny.
Show him what you got.

1034
01:04:03,440 --> 01:04:07,126
VETERAN: One night we get overrun.
I just curled up, waiting to die.

1035
01:04:08,320 --> 01:04:11,324
Till somebody dragged me
into this deserted mosque.

1036
01:04:11,880 --> 01:04:17,046
I look at the guy who just saved my butt.
He's just some hillbilly kid from Arkansas.

1037
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:19,604
Hey, at least you got out.

1038
01:04:19,800 --> 01:04:23,043
If they could put me back together,
I'd go back today.

1039
01:04:23,640 --> 01:04:24,687
For what?

1040
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:28,242
VETERAN: My unit. Listen, half
of them are still over there.

1041
01:04:28,440 --> 01:04:30,010
That don't make no sense.

1042
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:33,966
It's simple. Over there,
who you are in the world don't matter.

1043
01:04:35,040 --> 01:04:37,361
Fighting for your country
don't matter.

1044
01:04:38,560 --> 01:04:39,641
What does?

1045
01:04:40,640 --> 01:04:42,449
The guy next to you.

1046
01:04:42,640 --> 01:04:44,563
It's a brotherhood.

1047
01:04:45,760 --> 01:04:47,762
SALINAS: Let's go, boys.
You're running. Come on.

1048
01:04:48,160 --> 01:04:50,811
Come on, Danny.
Spartans for life, baby.

1049
01:04:51,160 --> 01:04:54,687
Live together. Die together.
Pick it up. Pick it up. Pick it up.

1050
01:04:54,840 --> 01:04:55,887
[BEEPING]

1051
01:04:56,040 --> 01:04:57,371
You wanna go faster?

1052
01:04:57,560 --> 01:04:58,766
Let's go faster.

1053
01:04:59,520 --> 01:05:00,601
[BEEPING]

1054
01:05:00,800 --> 01:05:03,804
[CROWD CHEERING]

1055
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:06,526
SALINAS:
Don't let us down, baby. Come on.

1056
01:05:06,920 --> 01:05:11,164
Let's go, baby. Come on, Danny. You got
this, dog. Don't stop, baby. Come on.

1057
01:05:11,360 --> 01:05:13,283
Do not stop on me. Do not stop.

1058
01:05:13,480 --> 01:05:15,528
You're a Spartan.
Don't stop, Danny.

1059
01:05:19,000 --> 01:05:20,570
I can't. I can't.

1060
01:05:20,760 --> 01:05:24,003
What?
He's gonna go forever.

1061
01:05:29,600 --> 01:05:31,170
No.

1062
01:05:31,520 --> 01:05:33,648
Not forever, Danny.

1063
01:05:34,360 --> 01:05:36,169
Just a little more than you.

1064
01:05:36,800 --> 01:05:38,450
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

1065
01:05:38,600 --> 01:05:40,443
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1066
01:05:40,840 --> 01:05:43,047
<i>♪ So keep believing ♪</i>

1067
01:05:43,200 --> 01:05:45,601
<i>♪ They will follow ♪</i>

1068
01:05:45,760 --> 01:05:48,047
<i>♪ Wake me up
Wake me up ♪</i>

1069
01:05:48,200 --> 01:05:50,362
<i>♪ Let the sunlight wake me up ♪</i>

1070
01:05:50,520 --> 01:05:55,367
<i>♪ I keep on dreaming about tomorrow ♪</i>

1071
01:05:55,520 --> 01:05:57,841
<i>♪ So wake me up
Wake me up ♪</i>

1072
01:05:58,200 --> 01:06:00,043
<i>♪ Wake me up ♪♪</i>

1073
01:06:02,560 --> 01:06:03,607
<i>BOB:
Long Beach Poly.</i>

1074
01:06:04,040 --> 01:06:07,726
By every measure, the best high-school
football team in the nation.

1075
01:06:07,920 --> 01:06:11,561
Offensive line,
average over 300 pounds.

1076
01:06:12,960 --> 01:06:16,043
Their starters. Beaser,

1077
01:06:16,280 --> 01:06:18,009
meet Buster Matthews.

1078
01:06:18,520 --> 01:06:21,205
Three hundred and thirty pounds
of pure aggression.

1079
01:06:21,400 --> 01:06:24,643
Poly runs 60 percent of their plays
behind him.

1080
01:06:24,840 --> 01:06:27,605
And you're gonna face him
the whole game.

1081
01:06:28,760 --> 01:06:30,649
But we have speed, right?

1082
01:06:31,080 --> 01:06:34,084
Their number-one wideout
clocks a 4.4 40.

1083
01:06:34,640 --> 01:06:37,883
I don't think we have anyone that fast.

1084
01:06:38,400 --> 01:06:41,244
Their key player?
Strong safety Darnell Bing.

1085
01:06:41,440 --> 01:06:44,967
Just committed to SC and plays
like he's been there three years.

1086
01:06:45,280 --> 01:06:48,966
Tayshon. You're a better match
for this guy's speed.

1087
01:06:49,160 --> 01:06:51,606
You're gonna start against Poly.

1088
01:06:55,920 --> 01:06:59,970
You're going into the most physically
demanding moment of your life.

1089
01:07:00,200 --> 01:07:01,884
[ALL GRUNTING]

1090
01:07:02,080 --> 01:07:03,730
Drive, drive, drive!

1091
01:07:05,600 --> 01:07:08,331
[ALL GRUNTING]

1092
01:07:09,000 --> 01:07:10,411
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1093
01:07:10,560 --> 01:07:13,370
<i>♪ I will, but you won't ♪</i>

1094
01:07:13,520 --> 01:07:16,364
<i>♪ Probably never
For as long as you live ♪</i>

1095
01:07:17,800 --> 01:07:20,201
<i>♪ Put on your coat ♪</i>

1096
01:07:20,360 --> 01:07:24,126
<i>♪ And meet me over by the end
Of the bridge ♪</i>

1097
01:07:24,480 --> 01:07:25,720
[GRUNTING]

1098
01:07:25,880 --> 01:07:29,521
<i>♪ Some people just won't move
That slow ♪</i>

1099
01:07:33,720 --> 01:07:36,121
Unh! Let me go again!
Let me go again!

1100
01:07:38,160 --> 01:07:39,650
<i>♪ They don't get me ♪</i>

1101
01:07:39,800 --> 01:07:40,847
Unh!

1102
01:07:41,680 --> 01:07:45,446
<i>♪ They don't break me
Don't hate me ♪</i>

1103
01:07:45,880 --> 01:07:49,043
Way to go, Beaser! Way to go!
All the way to the line.

1104
01:07:49,240 --> 01:07:52,483
<i>♪ They don't get me
They don't know me ♪♪</i>

1105
01:07:56,080 --> 01:07:57,127
<i>TERRY:
One tradition...</i>

1106
01:07:58,120 --> 01:08:02,170
<i>that defined this program
is the willingness of our players</i>

1107
01:08:02,360 --> 01:08:05,330
to share their emotions
at the end of these meetings.

1108
01:08:05,560 --> 01:08:07,005
This team hasn't done that.

1109
01:08:07,200 --> 01:08:11,524
You guys are still carrying around the
stigma of losing the streak. Forget that.

1110
01:08:12,520 --> 01:08:13,931
Forget it.

1111
01:08:16,320 --> 01:08:17,367
Open up.

1112
01:08:18,760 --> 01:08:20,728
Talk to each other.

1113
01:08:38,440 --> 01:08:41,091
My brother was captain
of the 2000 team.

1114
01:08:41,280 --> 01:08:44,250
In four years, he never lost one game.

1115
01:08:46,480 --> 01:08:50,610
When we blew the streak,
I couldn't look him in the eye.

1116
01:08:52,960 --> 01:08:54,883
I'm done with that.

1117
01:08:55,600 --> 01:08:58,410
Everything we've been through
was for a reason:

1118
01:08:58,600 --> 01:09:00,648
To bring us together.

1119
01:09:01,400 --> 01:09:03,368
I love you guys.

1120
01:09:04,320 --> 01:09:08,166
I will die on that field
before I let you down.

1121
01:09:08,360 --> 01:09:11,125
Collapse. Not die.

1122
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:14,048
It's just a high-school football game.

1123
01:09:14,800 --> 01:09:16,370
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1124
01:09:18,480 --> 01:09:21,006
I've been on this team four years.

1125
01:09:21,200 --> 01:09:24,283
I've never once played
in a varsity football game.

1126
01:09:26,040 --> 01:09:28,566
I mean, I'm not good enough.

1127
01:09:29,240 --> 01:09:33,325
And that's okay, because
the greatest moments of my life

1128
01:09:33,880 --> 01:09:36,724
were the times I've spent on this team
with you.

1129
01:09:37,400 --> 01:09:40,802
I've never been prouder of anything
than being a Spartan.

1130
01:09:41,440 --> 01:09:43,807
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1131
01:09:50,360 --> 01:09:55,207
When we first watched Poly's film,
and I saw Buster Matthews...

1132
01:09:56,560 --> 01:09:58,483
I was scared.

1133
01:09:59,760 --> 01:10:03,845
Then I remembered something Coach
Lad told us on my first day of practice.

1134
01:10:04,800 --> 01:10:07,007
"Face your fears."

1135
01:10:07,800 --> 01:10:11,805
That night I pasted Buster's name and
his number on my ceiling above my bed.

1136
01:10:12,000 --> 01:10:14,685
And every night since,
no matter how tired I was,

1137
01:10:15,240 --> 01:10:16,810
I've been saying:

1138
01:10:17,000 --> 01:10:21,244
"Buster Matthews, number 79...

1139
01:10:22,040 --> 01:10:26,523
you are mine."

1140
01:10:27,560 --> 01:10:29,403
A hundred times every night.

1141
01:10:29,760 --> 01:10:31,842
I promise you, guys.

1142
01:10:32,760 --> 01:10:36,003
We're not gonna lose
because of Buster Matthews.

1143
01:10:47,840 --> 01:10:50,286
My old man is insane.

1144
01:10:52,120 --> 01:10:55,363
My mom used to keep him in line,
but he wore her out.

1145
01:10:56,640 --> 01:10:59,610
Once I made the team,
I thought it'd be better.

1146
01:11:01,880 --> 01:11:04,008
He became an animal.

1147
01:11:07,320 --> 01:11:09,288
I hated him.

1148
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:12,241
Funny thing is, what...

1149
01:11:12,440 --> 01:11:15,489
What saved me
was being on this team.

1150
01:11:16,320 --> 01:11:21,690
I used to play as hard as I could because
I thought that would make him happy.

1151
01:11:22,600 --> 01:11:24,329
And then I'd be happy.

1152
01:11:25,080 --> 01:11:28,402
You guys love me whether
I'm scoring touchdowns or not.

1153
01:11:30,880 --> 01:11:34,805
I was missing that,
and you guys gave it to me.

1154
01:11:38,000 --> 01:11:40,844
I could never repay you for that.

1155
01:11:43,640 --> 01:11:45,642
But come tomorrow...

1156
01:11:48,120 --> 01:11:50,361
I don't play for him.

1157
01:11:52,640 --> 01:11:54,005
<i>I</i> play for you.

1158
01:11:55,320 --> 01:12:00,201
ANNOUNCER: <i>Welcome to Veterans Stadium,
home of the Long Beach Poly Jackrabbits,</i>

1159
01:12:00,400 --> 01:12:03,483
<i>where the De La Salle Spartans
of Concord, California</i>

1160
01:12:03,680 --> 01:12:08,641
<i>have traveled to the Southland for this
matchup of powerhouse programs.</i>

1161
01:12:08,880 --> 01:12:12,327
<i>At the end of last season,
these were the top two teams</i>

1162
01:12:12,880 --> 01:12:16,805
<i>and this was hyped as the game
for the national championship.</i>

1163
01:12:17,080 --> 01:12:19,082
[RUMBLING]

1164
01:12:21,080 --> 01:12:23,481
[STOMPING]

1165
01:12:32,080 --> 01:12:35,323
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1166
01:12:35,480 --> 01:12:37,687
Dude, these guys are giants.

1167
01:12:39,360 --> 01:12:41,522
[CROWD CHEERING]

1168
01:12:46,040 --> 01:12:49,044
ANNOUNCER: <i>Poly is riding high
on 34 straight victories.</i>

1169
01:12:49,240 --> 01:12:52,926
<i>De La Salle's 151 -game-winning streak
ended two weeks ago</i>

1170
01:12:53,120 --> 01:12:57,205
<i>and the Spartans come into this game
with an abysmal 0 and 2 record.</i>

1171
01:12:57,400 --> 01:13:00,165
<i>This team is struggling
and is nowhere as talented</i>

1172
01:13:00,360 --> 01:13:02,124
<i>as previous De La Salle teams.</i>

1173
01:13:02,320 --> 01:13:04,721
<i>This is the toughest game
on their schedule</i>

1174
01:13:04,920 --> 01:13:06,968
<i>and the most pivotal
of their season.</i>

1175
01:13:07,160 --> 01:13:08,605
<i>If they can't get a win,</i>

